<Base title="SocialProof for Interior Designers — Client Testimonials That Win Projects | SocialProof" description="Interior designers: turn happy clients into compelling testimonials that win new projects. SocialProof makes it easy to collect and display client reviews on your portfolio site.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Interior Designers
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Interior design is an intimate, high-stakes purchase. Clients are trusting you with their home — the place where they live, raise children, and relax. Before signing a contract, they scrutinize your portfolio and hunt for any sign of how it actually felt to work with you. SocialProof helps you capture authentic client testimonials and embed them alongside your best project photos, so your website converts visitors into discovery calls.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why testimonials matter more in design than almost any other field</h2>
      <p>Portfolios show what you create. Testimonials reveal what it's like to work with you — your process, communication, budget management, and how you handle the inevitable surprises. Prospective clients want both. A stunning before/after means little without a client saying "she listened to exactly what we wanted and delivered something even better."</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;">SocialProof gives you a testimonial widget that displays beautifully alongside your portfolio images — on desktop and mobile — so visitors get the full picture before they ever reach out.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What makes interior design testimonials convert</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Process transparency:</strong> "She broke down every decision so we always felt included, never overwhelmed."</li>
        <li><strong>Budget honesty:</strong> "Delivered on budget. No surprise invoices. That alone sets her apart."</li>
        <li><strong>Listening:</strong> "She heard what we said AND what we didn't say — the result is so us."</li>
        <li><strong>Project management:</strong> "Tradespeople showed up on time, every stage flowed — no chaos."</li>
        <li><strong>Transformation:</strong> "I cried when I walked in for the reveal. I've never felt that at home."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How SocialProof works for your design practice</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Embed the widget</strong> on your portfolio page, about page, or services page — 10 minutes, no developer required.</li>
        <li><strong>Send the collection link</strong> at project close — a single tap for your client, no account needed.</li>
        <li><strong>Review and approve</strong> submissions from your dashboard before they go live.</li>
        <li><strong>New testimonials appear automatically</strong> — your social proof compound-grows with every project.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">The perfect moment to ask</h2>
      <p>Interior designers often hesitate to ask for testimonials, worrying it feels transactional. It doesn't — it's a final act of connection at a moment when the client is thrilled. The best trigger: send your collection link the day the client shares a photo of themselves in the finished space. That's the emotional peak. A thoughtful ask at that moment gets a genuine, vivid response every time.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Works for every design specialty</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li>Residential interior design (full-service and e-design)</li>
        <li>Commercial and hospitality interiors</li>
        <li>Kitchen and bathroom remodels</li>
        <li>Staging for home sales</li>
        <li>Virtual and online design services</li>
        <li>Sustainable and biophilic design</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Start free — no credit card required</h2>
      <p>SocialProof's free plan gives you one active widget and unlimited testimonial collection. Collect from your last 5 clients this week and see what lands on your site.</p>
